They can do so within ten years of the ratification of the "Montego Bay Convention".
Where the continental shelf ends, the area of the ocean floor declared by the Convention as the "common heritage of humanity" begins.
No country has an exclusive position here anymore.
The right of exploitation in this area shall be granted by the international institution established by the Convention.
